This paper discusses the design and implementation of an autonomic system for service provision, which involves managing hosted web services and servers to run session-based traffic while meeting QoS constraints and SLAs. This topic is closely related to distributed computing (cs.DC), network infrastructure (cs.NI), software engineering (cs.SE), systems and control (cs.SY), and cryptography and security (cs.CR) as it involves optimizing system performance, collecting and analyzing data, and ensuring security and reliability.
